      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T01:30:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "isn\u0027t it possible to call this from a different thread anyway? It seems less confusing on balance if we just call this decodeAudio and continue to let the decoder thread call this function.\n\nBest would be to pass a closure to the decoder thread so that it becomes a simple worker thread consuming work items that VideoPlayer produces.\n\nAs is, it can be confusing, at least for a non-ffmpeg wizard like me, to see how all the parts fit together and where each part is used. VideoPlayer and the packet queues seem to have a bunch of state that is used in many locations :/",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 95,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 95,
        "endChar": 35
